section.text:
The
          United
			 States Housing Act of 1937(
            42 U.S.C. 1437 et seq.
          )is amended by adding at the
			 end the following new title:

subparagraph.text:
visiting
				door-to-door to each dwelling unit and providing such information to each
				resident;

restoring
				electric, gas, water, VAC., sewage, and elevator service as soon as
				possible;

developing a
				revised physical capital needs assessment to determine necessary repairs and
				rehabilitation of a public housing project;

paragraph.text:
backed-up critical computer files (such as
				contact information for residents and staff, rent and income calculations, and
				other information);

information
				regarding Federal, State, and local grant and loan programs and other resources
				related to disaster relief available to a covered public housing agency;

hosting annual workshops to train employees
				of public housing agencies on the disaster response and relief plans of such
				agencies and the proper implementation of such plans;
